tip.text: Happy hour prices here are ok. Interesting selection of beers. Food is ok, just above average.
Seafood tower is impressive and they have a good concept: shock-and-awe. Unfortunately on the day we were there, the seafood wasn't fresh. Otherwise, it's great. Service is fast and efficient.
Opens early at 7am. Great for people watching. Power plugs are located along the bottom of the cushioned seats facing out towards the store. Reliable wifi, but not fast.
Pretty good bak kut teh, worth a try. Free soup refills which is the standard in bak kut teh places. This is the clear, peppery Teochew version, not the dark brown, herbal Hokkien version.

tip.text: Swordfish collar is huge and tasty! But make sure they cook it through!
Nice hokkien mee, but pricey. I realised experience counts and the food's better when the old guy is at the stall and not the younger successor.
My number one favourite German restaurant in Tokyo. I cannot express my love enough. Bitburger beer is awesome with the food, and make sure you order one or ten Underbergs after your meal!

I love this place and all their grilled fish dishes!!!

tip.text: Fantastic noodles here. I like the classic wonton noodles the best.
Fantastic lor mee! They open early so you can have it for breakfast too. Truly exceptional preparation for a dish that's hard to find usually in hawker centres.

tip.text: Love this place! Great views and ambience and the food is so honest-to-goodness delicious and not just made to look good. Will be back!

tip.text: No doubt they are serious about their coffee. Unfortunately their barista told me they only use light roast coffee beans. This turns out a thin, watery and very acidic brew which is not to my taste.
A very cozy cafe with just the appropriate amount of hipster-ness; I don't appreciate hipsters but this place works. Strong reliable free wifi as I can stream Netflix here. Coffee is above average.
One of the nicest Starbucks in Singapore. Great views, located in an historic building. It is also a Starbucks Reserve store, meaning you get beans and brew methods not available in a normal store.

tip.text: Amazing noodles! Delicious wantons! I prefer the squid wanton over the pork ones. The broth used has been painstakingly made. A gem of a place in this neighbourhood. I will be back for more!
